remarks: A nonempty, bounded-above set of reals has a supremum.  Axiom 22 of 22 for real and complex numbers, derived from ZF set theory.  (This restates ~ ax-pre-sup with ordering on the extended reals.) (Contributed by NM, 13-Oct-2005.)
statement:
axsup $p |- ( ( A C_ RR /\ A =/= (/) /\ E. x e. RR A. y e. A y < x ) -> E. x e. RR ( A. y e. A -. x < y /\ A. y e. RR ( y < x -> E. z e. A y < z ) ) ) $.
$d A x y z $.
